Faradaic efficiency test was carried out in a custom-designed air-tight H-type electrochemical cell (H-cell, Chinese patent, CN201410777273.7) with an illumination window in the sidewall of the reactor, through which illumination can be applied to the photocathode. The cathode was connected to a gas circulation system with a tenport value (VICI) for online sampling to a gas chromatograph (GC, Agilent, 7890B) for H2 gas product detection. Before the start of the reaction, both the electrolyte and circulation system were purged with N2 (≥ 99.995%) for 30 min to remove air. After that, continuous N2 with a flow of 30 sccm was purged to the electrolyte during the test. The Faradaic efficiency for H2 production of the Si photocathode was calculated according to Eq. (3):3φF(%)=QexpQtheo=N×n(J×t)/(q×NA)×100%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
